{{/*
  tab_agents.gohtml — Agents tab placeholder (Phase 2c S5 polish).

  Phase 2c renders this tab as a non-clickable "coming soon" stub so the
  tab navigation surfaces all four planned tabs from day one rather than
  hiding the slot until 2d ships. The body documents what 2d will bring
  so a returning user (or a future Claude-Code session reading the
  rendered HTML) sees the roadmap without needing the plan file open.

  Phase 2d (see ~/.claude/plans/tracelab-phase-2d-agents.md, drafted
  after 2c-Closure) adds the KI-Agenten-Stack data domain on top of the
  app-log domain that 2c covers: a second persistence shape (agent
  spawn-tree rows), a second crash-equivalent (verdict + Lerneffekt
  capture), and a cross-domain link (mailbox / crew traffic edges
  joining the agent-tree to the live-tail event stream).

  Dot value: nil — the template is fully static.
*/}}
<section class="tl-tab-panel tl-agents" data-tab="agents" role="tabpanel">
  <h2>Agents</h2>

  <div class="tl-empty-state tl-coming-soon" role="status">
    <p class="tl-empty-state-title">Phase 2d — coming soon</p>
    <p class="tl-empty-state-body">
      The Agents tab will surface the KI-Agenten-Stack as a second data
      domain alongside the app-log surfaces of Phase 2c:
    </p>
    <ul class="tl-empty-state-list">
      <li><strong>Skill-Spawn-Tree:</strong> visualises which skills
        spawned which sub-skills inside a run, who reports up to whom.</li>
      <li><strong>Token-Usage &amp; Duration:</strong> per-spawn token
        cost, wall-clock duration, and budget burn-down so the cost of
        a multi-agent run is visible end-to-end.</li>
      <li><strong>Verdict &amp; Lerneffekt:</strong> the QS verdict
        captured per spawn (freigabe / rückgabe / eskalation) plus the
        post-run Lerneffekt note for the persona memory layer.</li>
      <li><strong>Mailbox &amp; Crew-Traffic edges:</strong>
        cross-references between the agent tree and the live-tail event
        stream so a crashing app surface can be traced back to the agent
        spawn that ran it.</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="tl-empty-state-footer tl-muted">
      Tracked in <code>~/.claude/plans/tracelab-phase-2d-agents.md</code>
      after the Phase 2c FF-merge.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>
